text.textPath: but animation is more, says the artist: it's the fish in the water. Motion creates emotion.

g.text: Plus, honor is in the dollar, kid. So banquish all evangelists and send in the real art.
**paradigm-shifting SVG walks your dog and Flash can't** is what we DON'T need to hear.
Developers are not buying adjectives. We're not going to take it, never did and never will.
But show working CODE and all the young dudes will FOLLOW FOLLOW FOLLOW
code speaks louder than words. And there is water at the bottom of the ocean.

g.text: And now, for an eastern half. an eastern half. an eastern half. an eastern half. an eastern half.
The designer+developer most be ready to know all the ways to attain a goal.
Through experience, a technology becomes a Way. Through ignorance of others,
a technology becomes a creed. It is bad to exchange an opportunity for a limitation.
It is bad to exchange a tool for dead weight. And so, the developer listens to the problem.
And so the great developer wants to know all Ways, and pray to none.
If one understand things in this manner, all Ways will give their best to one's purposes.
